review_blob: There was so little malt presence it was hard to finish.  It had a great amber color and nice amber head.  I would not drink tis again.

This beer poured like spent motor oil.  It had an amazing bouquet of dark malts, dark corn syrup with a chewy mouthfeel.  I loved the alcohol coming through in the finish.  A great find if you can get it.
One of my all-time favorite beers.  This tastes just like the beer has been smoked.  Loved it!

Amazing flavor of cherries is blasting out.  Tastes like fresh cherry pie.  I may have had a skunky bottle, but the nose was slightly smelling of wet cardboard.  Overall i enjoyed it immensely and hope the second bottle i have smells better.
A cheaper cousin to the expedition stout.  It has a slightly watered down mouthfeel for a special double stout.  Very dark with strong coffee, toffee, and chocolate flavors.
This beer was heavy, syrupy and amazing.  There is a huge amount of dark barley and coffee coming through.  I would buy it over and over
